	<doc for="CodeDirectionExpression">
		<summary>
			<para> Represents an expression used as a method invoke
      parameter along with a reference direction indicator. </para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para><see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeDirectionExpression"/> can represent a parameter passed to a
   method and the reference direction of the parameter. </para>
			<para>The <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeDirectionExpression.Expression"/> property indicates the
expression to qualify with a direction. The <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeDirectionExpression.Direction"/> property indicates the direction of the
parameter using one of the <see cref="System.CodeDom.FieldDirection"/> enumeration values.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates use of a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeDirectionExpression"/> to specify a field direction modifier for an
   expression to pass as a method parameter.</para>
